5. Correlation:-
Identity correlation
Correlation rules
Account linking

1️⃣ Correlation Kya Hota Hai
Correlation ka matlab hai:-
➡ Application se aaya hua account ko
➡ SailPoint ke identity se match karna.
Example:-
Application account:-
username = kishan.singh
email = kishan@gmail.com
Identity me:-
name = Kishan Singh
email = kishan@gmail.com
Agar email match ho gaya → account link ho jayega.

2️⃣ Identity Correlation:-
Identity correlation ka kaam hai:-
Account ko correct identity se match karna
Duplicate identities avoid karna
Identity cube update karna

3️⃣ Correlation Methods (Most Important):-
1️⃣ Attribute Based Correlation
Attributes match kiye jate hain.

Example:-
email
username
employeeId
Example rule:-
if(account.getAttribute("email").equals(identity.getEmail())){
    return true;
}

2️⃣ Rule Based Correlation;-
Developer custom rule likhta hai.
Use cases:-
Complex matching
Multiple attributes check

Example:-
String empId = account.getAttribute("employeeId");
if(empId != null && empId.equals(identity.getEmployeeId())){
    return true;
}

3️⃣ Multiple Attribute Correlation:-
Ek se zyada attributes match karte hain.
Example:-
firstname
lastname
department
Example:-
if(account.getAttribute("firstname").equals(identity.getFirstname())
 && account.getAttribute("lastname").equals(identity.getLastname())){
    return true;
}

4️⃣ Manager Based Correlation:-
Manager attribute ke base par match.
Example:-
account.manager = john
identity.manager = john

5️⃣ Email Based Correlation:-
Sabse common method.

Example:-
account.email = kishan@gmail.com
identity.email = kishan@gmail.com

4️⃣ Correlation Rules:-
Developer custom BeanShell rule likh sakta hai.
Rule type:-
Correlation Rule

Use cases:-
Complex identity match
Custom logic

Example:-
String email = account.getAttribute("mail");

if(email != null && email.equals(identity.getEmail())){
    return true;
}
return false;

5️⃣ Account Linking:-
Account linking ka matlab hai:-
➡ Application account
➡ Identity cube ke andar attach ho jata hai.

Example:-
Identity:-
Kishan Singh

Linked accounts:-
AD account
SAP account
Database account

6️⃣ Link Object:-
Link object store karta hai:-
Account attributes
Entitlements
Application name

Example attributes:-
nativeIdentity
application
displayName
entitlements

Example code:-
Link link = identity.getLink("ActiveDirectory");

7️⃣ Correlation Configuration:-
Admin UI me bhi configure kar sakta hai.

Steps:-
Application open karo
Correlation tab open karo
Attribute select karo

Example:-
Account attribute = email
Identity attribute = email

